By Shawn

“

Donald Trump once described himself as a neat freak, washing his hands regularly and drinking from a straw. The US media called him the most germ-phobic leader in US history.

”

The new crown pneumonia outbreak has grabbed headlines around the world. President Donald Trump, on the other hand, was initially "dismissive" in his rhetoric, even comparing it several times to seasonal flu.

But the CNN quoted a source close to Donald Trump on Thursday as saying he was actually concerned about his close contact with a confirmed patient.
Brazilian presidential spokesman Fabio Wajngarten, who met with Donald Trump at the weekend, was confirmed infected on the 12th. The Brazilian president, Jair Bolsonaro, and other members of the visiting delegation were also tested, and no one is showing symptoms. Bosonaro had dinner with Donald Trump during his visit to the United States.
Donald Trump bowed to the Irish prime minister, Leo Varadkar, in a meeting on Sunday, the Guardian reported.
In a 2017 Newsweek story, DONALD TRUMP claimed to be a GERMOPHOBE, washing his hands frequently and drinking from a straw. Politico reported something similar last year: Donald Trump is the most germ phobic leader in U.S. history. The first thing he did after shaking hands during the campaign was to ask his assistant to hand him hand sanitizer; he sent in a medic when he spotted someone coughing on Air Force One. Officials close to him say that once someone nearby coughs or sneezes, Donald Trump makes a gesture to keep them away from him.
Other analysts said Donald Trump was trying to play down the outbreak, apparently in an attempt to minimise its impact on the US economy and his re election prospects.
As the US election nears, the new crown epidemic has also become a "grab bag" for US politicians. Donald Trump's political rival, the Democratic presidential candidate Biden, condemned Donald Trump's travel ban on Europe the day before in a speech on December 12th, he said any effort to downplay the epidemic or spread misinformation would only exacerbate it.
Earlier in the day, Donald Trump said he was not concerned about possible exposure to the virus. Donald Trump said he and Bosonaro sat next to each other at dinner and it was unclear whether Vaughan Kato was there, but they had done nothing unusual, so there was nothing to worry about.
White House spokeswoman Stephanie Grisham said in a statement that Donald Trump and vice president Michel Pensée had had little contact with Worne and did not appear to have any symptoms. So they don't need to be tested.
But he was seen standing next to Donald Trump, along with Michel Pensée, in a photo posted on social media. In another live video, Bossonaro, Donald Trump and other members of the delegation gather to talk, with Worne standing behind Donald Trump.
The first on the right is Worne. Photograph: Fox News Channel
Other U.S. officials who have been in contact with the Brazilian delegation have said they will segregate themselves, including Republican Senator Scott of Florida and Senator Graham of South Carolina, who has been in close contact with Donald Trump. Scott said in a statement that his doctors had advised him that the risk of infection was low and that there was no need for testing or quarantine, but that he had decided to isolate himself for the sake of the health and safety of the American people.
In addition, at least five members of Congress have isolated themselves since this week for having had close contact with a clinician while attending the conservative political action conference (CPAC) late last month, among them was Donald Trump's newly appointed White House Chief of Staff, Mark Meadows. Donald Trump also attended the event, but was said to have had no direct contact with the person who was diagnosed.
However, two of the five sequestered members of Congress had recently been in close contact with Donald Trump, who was aboard Air Force One with Florida Congressman Gates. Gates, who also spoke to Worne, said Monday that he had tested negative for the new coronavirus.
Pelosi, a Democrat and President of the Chamber of Deputies of Tunisia, had also called for Donald Trump to be tested, but the White House insisted that Donald Trump was in excellent health and did not need to be tested
The World Health Organization (WHO) says the new coronavirus appears to be more dangerous for people over 60 WHO already have other diseases. Donald Trump, 73, has shown no apparent discomfort in recent public appearances. In November, the White House released the results of a medical exam that showed Donald Trump was healthy and "full of life. ".
As of 22:00 on the 12th (10:00 on the 13th) , there had been 1,663 confirmed cases and 40 deaths, according to real-time statistics released by the Johns Hopkins University.
Before the virus, everyone is equal, high-ranking national politicians are also unable to "immunity. ". In addition to Donald Trump and Bosonaro, the wife of Canadian Prime Minister Trudo was also diagnosed on the 12th. Trudeau's office said in a statement on the same day that the prime minister would begin self-imposed isolation for 14 days, but as no symptoms had yet emerged, doctors recommended no tests.
Earlier there were reports that Cambodian Prime Minister Hun Sen was infected after he went to the port to greet passengers of the ship. But Hun Sen appeared before a full session of Congress on the morning of the 13th to break the rumour mill.
Australian Home Minister Peter Dutton was also diagnosed on the 13th, three days after a meeting with Prime Minister Morrison, Finance Minister Fredenburg and other cabinet members. He was not wearing a mask at the time.
At least seven senior Iranian officials, including First Vice President Jahangiri and female Vice President Abtekar, were confirmed to be infected. The day before her diagnosis, she had not been wearing a mask and was attending a cabinet meeting in Tehran with Iranian President Rohani and a number of ministers. A member of Iran's Supreme Leader Ali Khamenei's Advisory Council has died of new pneumonia.
Also confirmed was Nadine Dorries, the Deputy Minister of the Department of Health, who attended a reception with Prime Minister Johnson on the day of the diagnosis.
Prime Minister of Slovakia Pellegrini was admitted to hospital late last month with a high fever and an acute upper respiratory tract infection, before news emerged that he had new crown pneumonia. But PELLEGRINI himself took to social media to dispel the rumor that it was "nonsense" .
